text.tspan: Rd : Output/Destiny register of the instruction.
Rn : Source and Operand 2 register/value. In P1 could be output/Destiny register.
When Rn is used as a register, only the four lowest bits are used.
When Rn is used as a value, the full Rn extensión is used as a inmediate value.
M = 0 and L = 0 -> Rn is a source register (only the LSB 4 bits).
M = 1 and L = 0 -> Rn is an IMMEDIATE value.
M = 1 and L = 1 -> Rn is the 32-bit immediate value following the double word.
